name: Bristol's Rainshine, Millenium Part 3: Buildings astride Millennium Promenade
description: We had stopped to decide whether to turn back to our original plan for crepes, or to find somewhere for a coffee and cake as the rain looked like it might be blowing in. The profile of the buildings together against the sky looked great but was too big for the lens I had, so I took a few and ended up joining two together. At Harbour Inlet, Millennium Promenade, shot from down by The Boathouse Units. | Two photograph panorama, 5172x5423px | f/5.6, 1/500s, 50mm | Canon 400D and Lightroom | Photographed 2nd June 2021 on a walk around the harbourside with Julia.
